author: mmathews@times-news.com(Mike Mathews)
title: Unbeaten Fort Hill sweeps Frankfort
text:
Unbeaten Fort Hill sweeps Frankfort FROM STAFF REPORTS The Cumberland Times-News Posted on Oct 6, 2015 by Mike Mathews 
SHORT GAP, W.Va. – Bailey Godlove had six service points, 12 kills, two blocks and five digs, while Skylar Barbe added 11 kills and 10 digs as Fort Hill remained unbeaten with a 3-0 win over Frankfort in Appalachian Mountain Athletic Conference volleyball Monday evening. 
The Sentinels won by scores of 25-16, 25-21 and 25-20 to improve their overall record to 7-0. 
Ny McGraw had 10 kills and a block and Makenna Smith three points, 29 assists and seven digs for Fort Hill. 
Hanna Slider had a triple-double for Frankfort (15-8-1) with 10 kills, 13 assists and 17 digs. Caitlin Davis added six kills, three digs, two aces and a block, Lindsay Greaser had seven digs and 16 assists and Madi Pfaff seven kills and 12 digs. 
Fort Hill won the jayvee match 25-18, 25-21 with Briana Towell getting eight points, six kills and 11 digs, Kayla Riley 13 assists, eight points and two digs, and Savannah Barbe 15 digs. 
Savannah Jenkins had three aces, three digs and five assists, Kayla Grose four kills and seven digs, Lauren Whiteman three kills and 13 digs, Alli Hockaday two kills and 12 digs and Hannah Dorsey three kills, four digs and five assists for the Frankfort jayvees (6-3). 
Fort Hill plays at Southern on Wednesday. Frankfort travels to Philip Barbour on Thursday, and will host Washington, East Hardy and Philip Barbour in a Saturday quad at 10 a.m. 
Allegany 3Hyndman 1 
CUMBERLAND — Micah Wormack finished with 21 kills, leading Allegany to victory over Hope for Hyndman. 
The Campers won the first two sets, 25-21 and 25-22. After losing the third set, 19-25, the Campers closed out the match in the fourth set, winning 25-20. 
In addition to Wormack’s effort, Autumn Holt added 31 assists, eight points and five digs. 
Chanel Porter had 21 digs and five points and Carmen Love finished with 11 kills. 
The Campers won the jayvee game, 25-18, 24-26 and 15-12. 
For the Campers, Morgan Chaney recored 18 digs and six kills, and Alayzia Wood had seven kills, five digs and four assists. 
Allegany (3-4) hosts Northern today. 
Northern 3, Calvary 0 
ACCIDENT — Northern defeated Calvary in straight sets, 25-19, 25-18 and 25-12. 
Kendra Friend led the way for the Huskies, finishing with 17 points. Samantha Kennell added 10 points. 
Hannah Bosley and Alexis Bagley finished with six digs each. 
Northern (3-6) will play today at Allegany. 
Bishop Walsh 3, Lighthouse 0 
CUMBERLAND — Bishop Walsh defeated Lighthouse in straight sets, 25-15, 25-11 and 25-6, on Monday evening. 
Abby Sensabaugh led the way for the Spartans, recording 11 aces and seven kills. 
Maria Castiglia added eight aces while Elizabeth Crites had three aces.
